Explanation:
We use nested loops to iterate through all possible pairs of elements from the two arrays. For each pair, we calculate the three differences and add them together. The outer loop ensures that each element from the first array is compared with every element from the second array. The time complexity is O(n^2), where n is the length of the arrays. Since the space complexity is O(1) due to using a constant amount of space for the max_abs_val variable, the solution has low energy implications.

